Problem Statement: Optimizing Food Waste Management in Event Planning using Generative AI.

The event industry often struggles with the logistics of largescale catering, where organizers must manage meal planning for hundreds or thousands of guests. A major challenge in this process is the lack of a data to predict food waste before an event even begins. Currently, most planners rely on rough estimates and making it safe by over-ordering, which leads to massive amounts of perfectly edible food ending up in the trash. This creates unnecessary costs and puts a heavy strain on the environment. Manual planning is often inaccurate and does not account for the specific variables that influence waste. The goal of this project is to build an intelligent, AI-powered tool that analyses event-specific data, such as guest counts, menu types, duration, and service styles, etc.. to generate accurate waste predictions. This tool will assist event managers in making informed, sustainable ordering decisions, ensuring that food is used efficiently and waste is reduced from the very start.
